VARIABLE RBDOCK
;----------------------River Hawk------------------------
NUMBER 3300
NAME In the water, near boat
DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are in the water next to a stout riverboat that towers above you. You see
several openings along its sides and a rope ladder leading back to the main
deck.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;---opening-----
ITEM 0 72  VAL2=2365
;---rope ladder------
ITEM 1 1108 VAL2=2350
;---------------------------------------
NUMBER 2350
NAME River Hawk, Forward Main Deck
DAY_LIGHT 
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are on the forward deck of a stout riverboat that carries goods up and
down the river for the towns along the Trazilar river. It is wide of beam
and rather square shaped. A paddle wheel aft push it through the water at
a good rate of speed for something so large. Large double doors lead into
the cargo hold. A ladder leads up to the deck above. When docked, a gang-
plank is extended to the shore.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;---------cargo bay doors---------
ITEM 0 65 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=97 VAL1=10 VAL2=2351 VAL3=2350 CLOSED LOCKED
;--------ladder to cabin deck-------
ITEM 1 1108 VAL2=2352
IFPREVERB TAP 0
	IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO ALL The riverboat docks as you watch, deckhands lower a gangplank.
		NEWITEM 2 412 ADJ1=290 ADJ2=355 VAL2=1654
		AFFECT 1654
		ECHO ALL A riverboat docks as you watch, deckhands lower a gangplank.
		NEWITEM 5 412 ADJ1=290 ADJ2=355
		NEWITEM 6 1774
		AFFECT 2350		
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB POKE 0
	IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO ALL The deckhands raise a gangplank, and the river boat chruns away from the dock.
		REMOVEITEM 2
		AFFECT 1654
		ECHO ALL The deckhands raise a gangplank, and the river boat chruns away from the dock.
		REMOVEITEM 5
		REMOVEITEM 6
		AFFECT 2350		
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH 0
	IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO ALL The riverboat docks as you watch, deckhands lower a gangplank.
		NEWITEM 2 412 ADJ1=290 ADJ2=355 VAL2=1665
		AFFECT 1665
		ECHO ALL A riverboat docks as you watch, deckhands lower a gangplank.
		NEWITEM 5 412 ADJ1=290 ADJ2=355
		NEWITEM 6 1774
		AFFECT 2350		
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PULL 0
	IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO ALL The deckhands raise a gangplank, and the river boat chruns away from the dock.
		REMOVEITEM 2
		AFFECT 1665
		ECHO ALL The deckhands raise a gangplank, and the river boat chruns away from the dock.
		REMOVEITEM 5
		REMOVEITEM 6
		AFFECT 2350		
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFITEM 2
        EQUAL RBDOCK ITEMVAL2
        IFPREVERB GO 2
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO PLAYER You make your way up the short gangplank onto the dock.
                ECHO OTHERS %N makes %h way up the short gangplank onto the dock.
                MOVE RBDOCK
                AFFECT RBDOCK
                ECHO OTHERS %N makes %h way up the short gangplank from the ferry toward you.
                AFFECT 2350
        ENDIF
ENDIF
;----------------------------------------------------------
NUMBER 2351
NAME River Hawk, Cargo Hold
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT 
INDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
You are in the cargo hold of a huge commercial boat that carries goods between
towns on the Trazilar River. Typical cargos include agricultural products,
leather, trade goods, and of the most value, caravan goods from the far west.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;-----------cargo bay doors---------
ITEM 0 65 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=97 VAL1=10 VAL2=2350 VAL3=2350 CLOSED LOCKED
;-----------trapdoor to slug deck-------
ITEM 2 550 ADJ1=319 VAL1=10 VAL2=2365 VAL3=2350 LOCKED CLOSED
IFPREVERB SMELL -1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You smell something rather nasty in here.
	ECHO OTHERS %N sniffs the air and makes a face.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB SEARCH -1
	CLEARVERB
	RANDOM DUMMY1 1 10 0
  	IFVAR DUMMY1 > 8
		ECHO PLAYER You find a trapdoor.
		ECHO OTHERS %N bends over and brushes %h hand across a trapdoor.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
