NUMBER 2356
NAME River Hawk, Corinth's Cabin
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT 
INDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
The cabin is on the port side aft of the Captain's cabin. A windowed door leads
out. The aft bulkhead has a mural of a tree in autumn foliage. An orange
curtain along the forward bulkhead hides his hunting clothes. He hangs his
weapons and boots from pegs on the remaining bulkhead. His bed is well made.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 65 ADJ1=319 VAL1=10 VAL2=2353 VAL3=2350 UNLOCKED CLOSED
