NUMBER 2357
NAME River Hawk, Calyx's Cabin
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT 
INDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
The cabin is on the starboard side aft of Captain's cabin. A windowed door
leads out. The aft bulkhead has a mural of small shrubs leafing out in spring.
Calyx sleeps in a pile of blankets and rushes on the floor. There is a pale
green curtain along the forward bulkhead, but nothing is behind it. Although
there are pegs and shelves on the bulkheads, Calyx rarely uses them. Instead
he just drops his things on the floor.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 65 ADJ1=319 VAL1=10 VAL2=2354 VAL3=2350 UNLOCKED CLOSED
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The door is made of fine teak and has a small round stained glass window. 
*DESCRIPTION_END
;------------------------------------------------------------------
NUMBER 2358
NAME River Hawk, Bosun Tam's Cabin
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT 
INDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
The cabin is on the starboard side aft of Calyx's. A windowed door leading out.
Although small and containing many items, the cabin seems roomy due to the
Bosun's rigid discipline. He has an abundance of built-in drawers and shelves,
with their contents always placed exactly the same way. His clothes are tightly
rolled and stowed, and every inch of storage is used. The wood of the cabin
shines with a rich warmth. Brass hinges and handles sparkle merrily. Intricate
knotted rope-work is displayed decoratively. A small locker contains bright
ribbons. He sleeps in a hammock, which is carefully put away when not in use.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 65 ADJ1=319 VAL1=10 VAL2=2354 VAL3=2350 UNLOCKED CLOSED
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The door is made of fine teak and has a small round stained glass window. 
*DESCRIPTION_END
;---------------------------------------------------------------------
