NUMBER 2360
NAME River Hawk, Deckhand's Cabin
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT 
INDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
The largest cabin, with three windows and one windowed door leading out. There
are three sets of bunk beds fastened to the bulkheads in the front of the
cabin. Each set is a stack of three bunks, so that there are nine sleeping
places in the cabin. Each crewman has a footlocker, either under the lowermost
bunk or under a window. In the center of the cabin is a small table with three
chairs.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 65 ADJ1=319 VAL1=10 VAL2=2353 VAL3=2350 UNLOCKED CLOSED
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The door is made of fine teak and has a small round window. 
