NUMBER 2365
NAME River Hawk, Slug Deck
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT 
INDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
This is an incredible room. It runs the full length of the boat. Along each
side of the ship are wooden treadmills upon which slide three huge giant slugs!
These creatures are easily 10 feet long and massive. The treadmills turn as the
slugs glide along their slime trails. Loud gearing connect these treadmills to
huge flywheels that are connected to the paddle wheels on each side of the 
River Hawk. Slug stalls fore and aft house resting slugs. This is where the
huge beasts are washed and fed. A trapdoor leads up to the Cargo Hold and
a hatch leads down into the bilges.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 550 ADJ1=319 VAL1=10 VAL2=2351 VAL3=2350 LOCKED CLOSED
ITEM 1 1466 ADJ1=319 VAL1=10 VAL2=2366 UNLOCKED CLOSED
IFENTRY -1
	ECHO PLAYER Phew! Does it stink in here!
	ECHO OTHERS As %N enters the Slug Deck %s wrinkles %h nose.
ENDIF
;---------------------------------------------------------------
NUMBER 2366
NAME River Hawk, Bilges
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT 
INDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
The bilges are dark, confining, awash with water and slime, and exceedingly
dangerous due to the chaos of gears, belts shafts and the return loop of the
slugways. No person in his right mind would even enter the bilges, much less
work there. A hatch leads up to the Slug Deck.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 1466 ADJ1=319 VAL1=10 VAL2=2365 UNLOCKED CLOSED
IFENTRY -1
	ECHO PLAYER Phew! Does it stink in here!
	ECHO OTHERS As %N enters the Bilges %s wrinkles %h nose.
ENDIF
